                                           java.lang.String AddressName,
                                           long FactoshiAmount)
        addECOutput - Adds output value and destination for an Entry Credit (not factoid) transaction this will create entry credits at the current exchange rate. if you need to create a specific number of entry credits, work out the number of factoshi to use in advance
        Parameters:
        TransactionName - String - Transaction name only exists while building a Factoid send or entry credit conversion - Not useful persistent information
        AddressName - Address and or address name to send entry credits (Not factoid) to total of outputs ave to equal inputs
        FactoshiAmount - amounts are denominated in Factoshi (1/100000000 factoid)
        Returns:
        JSON document as string.

        {"Response":"Success adding EC Out","Success":true}

        Example:

        responseText=AddECOutput("TranCode1","sendingAddress",50000);

        responseText=AddECOutput("TranCode1","FAxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx",50000);
